3rd one, I don't know - the reason for the edit, I think some folks said 3 and some 4, total.<br>
<br>
The 4th, the real war, is the province of uberguilds, think of 10th ring war only more so - active fighting on 3 or more fronts, for long periods of time.<br>
<br>
I was interested in the fact that 4th war actually has some nice drops. If I can find out more, maybe we can do the 4th with intent to only get those drops, and not /win/ or something. However, in the waves thrown at the camps, it was noted that there were extreme necro npcs, who cast a "mad aoe fear" which often caused ALL people present to flee, basically even with high saves. They said it was odd because often you would get attacked while feared, and die, and not know until the fear wore off.<br>
The developer was interested in feedback for tuning purposes, and said there were some AAXP skills that this particular section was designed in mind with. The obvious ones are (melee only? War definitely : Fearless, battlecry? (AOE fearless on PCs), and AOE taunt).<br>
Given that kind of requirement, I think it's reasonable to say we ain't got a hope =p<br>
<br>
Prior to the last quest there are no drops, ie the previous quests are to (a) get you to the last one, and (b) get you trained.<br>
<br>
Ring of High Priest is aimed at 1 60ish, or 2 55+ / 50+ with 60s included. The drops are 60 spells, and high end items, or twink stuff that no-one's main capable of winning the ring would use. <br>
<br>
Burrower is a low end ubermob. Think Velk or Vind. But then acknowledge that it's got nice drops and so is permafarmed by folks who conceptually wouldn't normally bother.<br>
<br>
The mines outside acrylia are at best L-blue, I would say 95% green to me at 60. We aoe them for fun, since they are annoying, and grimlings are the scum of the moon. The named ones are l-blue, but offer a bit of a shock if you aren't prepared. Abilities we find scattered thru luclin, like summoning, no-stun, or no run mode alteration are common. I can solo em all, tho, realistically.<br>
<br>
The named inside are blue to 60, as is most of acrylia (LBlue scattered at worst), and have the same additional abilities noted above, but also have the zone random resists to nerf aoe (ie, some resist Magic, fire, stun, cold, etc, at random, 100%).<br>
<br>
Acrylia could be thought of as seb with less named, but a faster repop, aside from the fact that easily half the zone is "ring" based encounter placement / keyed entry to high level rings. The repop time makes up for this, but named drops don't really compare to seb, altho you will find more "fun" or interesting things. Toys. Things like +5% med ring, for example.<br>
<br>
Inner acrylia requires a dedicated uberguild to really attempt. One well versed in ring events.<br>
<br>
Ring of fire is a 55+ toy, with nice rewards. I would say uberguild to complete, and really aimed at 60s. <br>
<br>
The problem I see is that you have to accept you are going to die and loose /some/ xp, doing certain events. Before 60, that's not good. People get twitchy. At 60, it's no matter, once you secure the level, you are on 90% axp, and never worry about dying again. <p> - Tistalion, Just another druid</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/utistali0n.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tistali0n</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Stallion</span><br>  Posts: 660<br> <font color=#333333>(6/24/02 5:48:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling Forest / Acrylia &quot;ring&quot; quests overvi</span><hr size=1> Hmm, also : <br>
<br>
In traditional TRK manner, I hate to turn away interested folks. I do think the event is aimed at the listed 1 60 group (carefully chosen classes), or 2 55+ less carefully selected groups.  Actually, 1 group would be : 2 60 pal, 2 60 rog, 1 60 clr, 1 60 enc. Cleric would be shackled, you fight in doorway. <br>
That aside .. I am a bit ... hesitant .. about having lower level wis casters come .. but I haven't let that stop any doing so -) .. ATM I am putting it down to the fact that I want the shield, and that's greed, so I am ignoring it. Rest assured, once the ring kicks into wave 3 or 4, everyone feels needed, or contributes to their utmost, and I know it -)<br>
<br>
In traditional Tist manner, I am running these things by seeing who is on that I can get to come at the time, when I feel like it. <br>
<br>
Additionally, I know the baseline to "win", so I won't attempt it without saying "I think it's risky to attempt it" if I think we will not win, or even /may/ fail.<br>
<br>
Been right so far, too.<br>
<br>
<br>
Edit : Gah, posted before I was done, I hate IE6.<br>
<br>
What I would really like to do is take 3-4 groups, for whom this would be trivial, and farm the hell out of it for 4 hours, getting more spells than we will ever need, and hopefully loads of FT1 shields. <br>
